pcsc-tools
------------------------------------------
The pcsc-tools package contains some useful tools for a PC/SC user: pcsc_scan
regularly scans connected PC/SC smart card readers and prints detected events,
ATR_analysis analyzes smart card ATRs (Anwser To Reset), scriptor sends
commands to a smart card, and gscriptor does that from a GTK user interface.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.4.5-1
  libpcsclite1-1.9.9-1bl1
  perl_base-5.32.1-2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.39-1
  cygport-0.36.0-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  libpcsclite-devel-1.9.9-1bl1
  make-4.4-1

Canonical website:
  https://pcsc-tools.apdu.fr/

Canonical download:
  https://pcsc-tools.apdu.fr/pcsc-tools-1.6.2.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack pcsc-tools-1.6.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./pcsc-tools-1.6.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/pcsc-tools-1.6.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/pcsc-tools-1.6.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(pcsc-tools)
  /usr/bin/ATR_analysis
  /usr/bin/gscriptor
  /usr/bin/pcsc_scan.exe
  /usr/bin/scriptor
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/pcsc-tools.README
  /usr/share/doc/pcsc-tools/Changelog
  /usr/share/doc/pcsc-tools/LICENCE
  /usr/share/doc/pcsc-tools/README
  /usr/share/man/man1/ATR_analysis.1p.gz
  /usr/share/man/man1/gscriptor.1p.gz
  /usr/share/man/man1/pcsc_scan.1.gz
  /usr/share/man/man1/scriptor.1p.gz
  /usr/share/pcsc/smartcard_list.txt

